## 2. Clone this repository

1. Fork this repository to your github account. 

- Go to https://github.com/groxio-learning/otpv_2021 
- Click the `fork` button in the upper right corner
- Navigate to *your local version* (at something like https://github.com/your-github-account/otpv_2021 )
- copy the clone address to your clipboard. In the upper right, click `clone or download` then `copy to clipboard`

2. Clone your local version to your local machine. 

- Clone it. *REPLACE your-github-account with your account*:  

```
>  git clone https://github.com/your-github-account/otpv_2021.git
...clones repo...
cd otpv_2021
```

- Verify your remote: 

```
$ git remote -v
> origin  https://github.com/your-user/otpv_2021.git (fetch)
> origin  https://github.com/your-user/otpv_2021.git (push)
```


- If there's no origin, set it. Make sure you *replace your-github-account*:

```
otpv_2021> git remote add origin https://github.com/your-github-account/otpv_2021.git
```

- Verify your remote: 

```
$ git remote -v
> origin  https://github.com/your-user/otpv_2021.git (fetch)
> origin  https://github.com/your-user/otpv_2021.git (push)
```

- Set the upstream to the Groxio repo:

```
otpv_2021> git remote add upstream https://github.com/groxio-learning/otpv_2021.git
```

- Verify the remotes: 

```
> origin  https://github.com/your-user/otpv_2021.git (fetch)
> origin  https://github.com/your-user/otpv_2021.git (push)
> upstream  https://github.com/groxio-learning/otpv_2021.git (fetch)
> upstream  https://github.com/groxio-learning/otpv_2021.git (push)
```

